PTI | New Delhi , September 19 , 2011 21 : 00 Landslides and inclement weather today hampered rescue operations in quake - hit Sikkim as the death toll in the 6 . 8 magnitude tremblor mounted to 66 , including 39 in the Himalayan state . The earthquake , which struck last evening , left a trail of devastation damaging roads , buildings and other structures , uprooting mobile phone towers and snapping communication and power lines .